Package com.paulgreenlee.fn

Class Tuples

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.paulgreenlee.fn.Tuples
  • public class Tuples
extends java.lang.Object
    Simple container types. There is no facility for this in Java. If you want to return two values from a function, you have to create a new type to do so. The Record type in Java 15 reduces the overhead to creating a new simple type, but this may still be easier.

      • equal

        public static boolean equal​(Tuples.Tuple a,
                            Tuples.Tuple b)
        Compare two Tuples for equality. They must have the same cardinality and order to be considered equal. The types of the values are not explicitly compared. Objects.equals(...) is used to compare each pair of values in the two Tuples.
        Parameters:
        a - a tuple
        b - another tuple
        Returns:
        true if the two Tuples are the same
